title.narrative: Strengthening differentiated and quality HIV/AIDS treatment and care in the Republic of Guinea

description.narrative: Guinea - HIV - The Ministry of Health of the Republic of Guinea - MOH. This program has the following goals: Les nouvelles infections VIH sont réduites de 50% d’ici à fin 2023/New HIV infections are reduced by 50% by the end of 2023.. D’ici à fin 2023, la mortalité liée au VIH/sida est réduite d'au moins 62%/By the end of 2023, mortality from HIV / AIDS is reduced by at least 62%.. The objectives of this program are: Le taux de transmission du VIH de la mère à l’enfant est réduit à moins de 5%/Mother-to-child transmission rate reduced to less than 5%.. 90% des PVVIH sous ARV ont une charge virale indétectable à 12 mois en 2023/90% of PLHIV on ARVs have an undetectable viral load at 12 months in 2023.. Au moins 80% des populations clés (PS, UDI, HSH) et populations vulnérables (Miniers, routiers, hommes en uniforme, populations carcérales, pêcheurs) ont des comportements à moindre risque d’ici 2023/At least 80% of key populations (PS, IDU, MSM) and vulnerable populations (Miners, truckers, men in uniform, prison populations, fishermen) have lower risk behaviors by 2023.. Le taux de décès chez les patients coïnfectés TB/VIH est réduit de 70% d’ici à fin 2023/Death rate among TB/HIV co-infected patients reduced by 70% by the end of 2023.. 75% des adultes et enfants vivant avec le VIH bénéficient d’une prise en charge médicale, psychologique, sociale de qualité d’ici à 2023/75% of adults and children living with HIV receive quality medical, psychological and social care by 2023.. 90% des PVVIH connaissent leur statut sérologique et sont référés vers les services de soins/traitement d'ici 2023/90% of people living with HIV know their HIV status and are referred to care / treatment services by 2023.. Au moins 90% des adultes de 15-49 ans, y compris les prestataires de soins et de services ont des attitudes de non- stigmatisation et non- discrimination à l’égard des PVVIH d’ici à fin 2023/At least 90% of adults aged 15-49, including caregivers and service providers, have non-stigmatizing and non-discriminatory attitudes towards PLHIV by the end of 2023.

title.narrative: Coverage / Output indicator for GIN-H-MOH
Percentage of people living with HIV and on ART, who have a suppressed viral load at 12 months (<1000 copies/ml)
Number of people who were tested for HIV and received their results during the reporting period
Percentage of people on ART among all people living with HIV at the end of the reporting period

Timeliness of facility reporting: Percentage of monthly reports (for the reporting period) from large cohort HIV Care and Treatment (C&T) health facilities that are received on time per the national guidelines
Percentage of children (under 15) on ART among all children living with HIV at the end of the reporting period
Percentage of large cohort HIV Care and Treatment (C&T) health facilities that did not experience a stockout of more than 5 days for any of the HIV tracer drugs during the reporting period
Percentage of HIV-positive new and relapse TB patients on ART during TB treatment
Percentage of HMIS or other routine reporting units submitting timely reports according to national guidelines
Percentage of HIV-exposed infants receiving a virological test for HIV within 2 months of birth
Percentage of registered new and relapse TB patients with documented HIV status
Percentage of HIV-positive results among the total HIV tests performed during the reporting period

Completeness of facility reporting: Percentage of expected facility monthly reports (for the reporting period) from large cohort HIV Care and Treatment (C&T) health facilities that were actually entered into DHIS-2
Percentage of adults (15 and above) on ART among all adults living with HIV at the end of the reporting period
Percentage of people living with HIV initiated on ART who are screened for TB in HIV treatment settings
Percentage of pregnant women who know their HIV status
Percentage of people living with HIV currently receiving antiretroviral therapy
Percentage of ART sites that had a stock-out of any antiretroviral drugs during the reporting period
Percentage of HIV-positive women who received ART during pregnancy and/or labour and delivery
Percentage of people living with HIV newly initiated on ART who were screened for TB
Percentage of people living with HIV newly enrolled in HIV care started on TB preventive therapy
Percentage of PLHIV on ART who initiated TB preventive therapy among those eligible during the reporting period
